In a couple of hours now we are all going to be attacked by zombies.
Midnight will hit and All Hallow’s Eve will commence, the day when the land of the dead joins the land of the living. Witches will fly through the skies, zombies will stalk the earth, and children will prowl the streets hunting for sweet treats. A few jerks somewhere will probably smash pumpkins.
Fortunately we live in a modern age, filled with technology that can stave off disaster.
Any zombie survival kit should involve the basic elements of physical protection — rifle, crossbow, machete — but digital protection is also important.
Check out this infographic from NowSourcing on how to manage a zombie apocalypse using tech.
